               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r"/>-85r: Homily of the suffering, death of our Lord and savior, Jesus Christ, the life giver written by the three evangelists and virgins Bridget, Matilda, and Elizabeth, ድርሳነ፡ ማኅየዊ፡ ዘሕማማቲሁ፡ ወሞቱ፡ ለእግዚእነ፡ ወአምላክነ፡ ወመድኃኒነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዘጸሐፍዋ፡ ወንጌላዊያን፡ ወሠላስ፡ ደናግል፡ በርዜዳ፡ ወመልቴዳ፡ ወኤልሳቤጥ፡ . . . arranged For the days of the week: Monday (<locus target="#1r"/>), Tuesday (<locus target="#15r"/>), Wednesday (<locus target="#28r"/>), Thursday (<locus target="#40r"/>), Friday (<locus target="#56r"/>), Saturday (<locus target="#70r"/>), Sunday (<locus target="#85r"/>), unpublished, but see catalog entries for British Library Add. 16254 and AbbCat 29. F<locus target="#97r"/>-107r: Asmat Prayer based on the saying "The Fear of God is the Beginning of Wisdom" ቀዳሚያ ለጥበብ ፈሪሃ እግዚአብሔር በዝንቱ ፫ቱ አስማት...ክርስቲያኖስ, ክርስቲያኖስ, ክርስቲያኖስ, arranged for the days of the week: Monday (<locus target="#97r"/>), Tuesday (<locus target="#100v"/>), Wednesday (<locus target="#101r"/>), Thursday (<locus target="#102v"/>), Friday (<locus target="#103v"/>), Saturday (<locus target="#104v"/>), Sunday (<locus target="#105v"/>).  F<locus target="#1v"/> and passim mentions the owner, ኃይለ ማርያም and his wife, አመተ ማርያም. The artwork is signed. </summary>
